    "summary": "I am a research scientist at TNO location Petten, formerly the Energy research Center of the Netherlands ECN. I have a M.S. degree (1987) in applied physics and a Ph.D. degree (1992) in mechanical engineering, both from the Delft University of Technology. My dissertation work was on the structure of the turbulent boundary layer. \n\nI have been employed in wind energy since 1991. \n\nUp to 1999 I was mainly involved in experimental and computational wind turbine rotor aerodynamics. In this context I participated in four projects under the European Non-Nuclear Energy Programme and two Tasks of the International Energy Agency. In 1998 I got involved in wind energy meteorology, with emphasis on short-term prediction and wind resource assessment. Recent projects were on renewable energy forecasting, the wind (power) resource of the North Sea, the integration of wind power into the grid, the effect of wind farms on the wind resource, and the flow modelling aspects of wind farm control. With a brief excursion to the modeling and control of clusters of wind farms, I'm back in wind resource assessment.\n\nI was secretary of Netherlands Wind Energy Association NEWIN (2000-2006) and have been a member of the Steering Committee Wind Technology of KiviNiria (since 2003). My research interests include fluid dynamics (experimental as well as numerical), aerodynamics, turbulence, and statistics.\n\nSpecialties: Wind energy meteorology:\n* Wind power forecasting\n* Wind resource assessment",
